Goya (The Masters Collection)
Castle Books | 1980 | ISBN: 0890093571 | English | 72 pages | PDF | 7.8 MB

Goya, master of Spanish art, is one of the truly fascinating figures in art history. Although he gained fame as a painter of elaborate portraits for the aristocracy and the royal family, Goya was also capable of producing some of the most biting satire ever created. What appears to be a conflict is in fact the result of living in Spain during a period of treachery, corruption and decadence. It required cunning and courage as well as skill for Goya to survive and flourish in this atmosphere
